Ùª­jAttributesÙ¯‚€öpExtended SummaryÙ¯‚‚Ù¹‚Ù§yÉMorphological reconstruction by dilation is similar to basic morphological dilation: high-intensity values will replace nearby low-intensity values. The basic dilation operator, however, uses a structuring element to determine how far a value in the input image can spread. In contrast, reconstruction uses two images: a "seed" image, which specifies the values that spread, and a "mask" image, which gives the maximum allowed value at each pixel. The mask image, like the structuring element, limits the spread of high-intensity values. Reconstruction by erosion is simply the inverse: low-intensity values spread from the seed image and are limited by the mask image, which represents the minimum allowed value.€Ù¹‚Ù§ypAlternatively, you can think of reconstruction as a way to isolate the connected regions of an image. For dilation, reconstruction connects regions marked by local maxima in the seed image: neighboring pixels less-than-or-equal-to those seeds are connected to the seeded region. Local maxima with values larger than the seed image will get truncated to the seed value.€ögMethodsÙ¯‚€öeNotesÙ¯‚Ù¹‚Ù§x_The algorithm is taken from . Applications for greyscale reconstruction are discussed in  and .€öpOther ParametersÙ¯‚€öjParametersÙ¯‚…Ù°ƒdseedgndarrayÙ¹‚Ù§x\The seed image (a.k.a. marker image), which specifies the values that are dilated or eroded.€Ù°ƒdmaskgndarrayÙ¹‚Ù§xGThe maximum (dilation) / minimum (erosion) allowed value at each pixel.€Ù°ƒfmethodx {'dilation'|'erosion'}, optionalÙ¹‚Ù§y"Perform reconstruction by dilation or erosion. In dilation (or erosion), the seed image is dilated (or eroded) until limited by the mask image. For dilation, each seed value must be less than or equal to the corresponding mask value; for erosion, the reverse is true. Default is 'dilation'.€Ù°ƒeselemqndarray, optionalÙ¹‚Ù§x­The neighborhood expressed as an n-D array of 1's and 0's. Default is the n-D square of radius equal to 1 (i.e. a 3x3 square for 2D images, a 3x3x3 cube for 3D images, etc.)€Ù°ƒfoffsetqndarray, optionalÙ¹‚Ù§xŸThe coordinates of the center of the structuring element. Default is located on the geometrical center of the selem, in that case selem dimensions must be odd.€öfRaisesÙ¯‚€öhReceivesÙ¯‚€ögReturnsÙ¯‚Ù°ƒmreconstructedgndarrayÙ¹‚Ù§x+The result of morphological reconstruction.€ögSummaryÙ¯‚Ù¹‚Ù§x3Perform a morphological reconstruction of an image.€öhWarningsÙ¯‚€öeWarnsÙ¯‚€öfYieldsÙ¯‚€ö‡gSummarypExtended SummaryjParametersgReturnshExampleseNotesjReferencesx&/skimage/morphology/greyreconstruct.pyr<class 'function'>x!skimage.morphology.reconstructionÙ¯‚Ù´ƒ‘Ù±‚bknfimportÙ±‚`a Ù±‚bnnÙ¢„enumpyÙ „enumpyf1.22.3fmoduleenumpyfmoduleõÙ±‚`a Ù±‚akbasÙ±‚`a Ù±‚bnnÙ¢„bnpÙ „enumpyf1.22.3fmoduleenumpyfmoduleõÙ±‚`a
